Implement the private `do_identifier/1` function. It takes the raw identifier
string and cleans it into a safe SQL identifier. Strip out every character that
is not in `[A-Za-z0-9_]` (i.e. remove anything matching `[^a-zA-Z0-9_]`). Then:
